Class TablePostProcessor.MarkupProcessor

java.lang.Object
  threepio.tabler.TablePostProcessor.MarkupProcessor

Enclosing class:
TablePostProcessor
private abstract class TablePostProcessor.MarkupProcessor
extends java.lang.Object

MarkupProcessor is an abstract class that defines common functionality for other processing classes that are defined in and used in the TablePostProcessor. MarkupProcessor objects processMarkups the BBF markup in tables' cells.

processMarkups

void processMarkups(java.lang.String input,
                    Table t,
                    java.lang.String rowName,

                    int typeCol,
                    java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> refNames)
              throws java.lang.Exception
processMarkups processes the input string, possibly using the Table, Row, and integer passed, stripping the string of BBF markup, and processing aStatement as described in the Template.

Parameters:
input - - a string from the table.
t - - the table that the string is found in.
rowName - - the name of the row where a cell is being processed.
r - - the row that the string is found in.
typeCol - - the index of the column in the row that will have type information.
refNames - - reference ids mapped to reference names.
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - - because this has to be overridden by a class that actually does this.
